## Auto-Memory Protocol

The agent updates context files when it observes these triggers:

| Trigger | Action | Target File |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| Experiment completes | Log hypothesis, config, result, next steps | `context/experiments.md` |
| Bug resolved | Log root cause + fix | `context/conventions.md` |
| "remember", "always do", "convention" | Save preference/convention | `context/conventions.md` |
| Architecture discovery | Document module, data flow | `context/architecture.md` |

## Available Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `/init-eureka` | Scan project and generate CLAUDE.md |
| `/refresh-context` | Regenerate auto-sections from project state |
| `/experiment` | Create, launch, and track experiments |
| `/debug` | Systematic root-cause debugging |
| `/review` | Code review (YAGNI/KISS + research patterns) |
| `/scaffold` | Generate boilerplate (model, dataset, trainer, config, slurm) |
| `/viz` | Publication-quality plot generation |
| `/notebook` | Analysis notebook creation |
| `/submit-job` | SLURM job submission and monitoring |
| `/create-skill` | Author new skills or commands |
| `/contribute-skill` | Package a skill and open PR to claude-eureka |
| `/update-eureka` | Update installed commands and skills to latest version |

## Guidelines

- Prefer concise, precise technical responses
- Assume familiarity with PyTorch, Linux, standard ML tooling
- Don't add features beyond what's requested
- When debugging, always find root cause first (use /debug)
- Log experiment results to `.claude/context/experiments.md`
